The GM that let you down
a `` New GM '' that he expected to result from the bankruptcy process
a majority shareholder in the restructured company , dictating future product development and strategy

the specific hypothetical scenario where the management of GM wants to make one type of car , because it thinks that it is the right thing for the business , and the U.S. government wants to make another type of car
the right thing for the business
a question `` better addressed to the U.S. Treasury ''
